cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is about reinforcement learning (RL) using video prediction models to enable agents to solve Atari games with fewer interactions than model-free methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 

The paper also involves computer vision (CV) techniques for processing image observations, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely sub-category. 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of RL algorithms to control robotic systems (cs.RO - Robotics), which is another possible sub-category. 

The paper also involves the use of predictive models to enable agents to learn how the game works and predict which actions will lead to desirable outcomes, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of model-based RL algorithms, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category.
